radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated up to 1.4 cm in diameter with an appendicolith at the proximal appendix. There is free fluid and inflammatory fat stranding surrounding the appendix compatible with phlegmon. The lung bases are clear. No focal liver lesions, bile duct dilatation, or acute bone abnormality. Normal findings in liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, uterus, adnexa, rectum, bladder, and terminal ureters. Prominent right external iliac lymph nodes and mildly prominent lymph nodes in the right pelvis.
